The Green Waterhole Cave fossil deposit has not been directly dated, but the species composition of the assemblage suggests a Middle or Late Pleistocene age ( Pledge, 1980 ; Baird, 1985 ; Prideaux, 2004 , 2007). This falls within the Naracoortean land mammal age (
Megirian et al. , 2010
).
